Name: ID
Description: This is a unique identifying number for the pair of AIS transmissions described by the following data.

Name: MMSI_1
Description: This is the Maritime Mobile Service Identity of the first vessel.

Name: BaseDateTime_1
Description: Transmission time of the first vessel's AIS signal. Should be in the form MM/DD/YYYY HH:MM:SS UTC.

Name: Timestamp_1
Description: Transmission time of the first vessel's AIS signal. Should be in the form MM/DD/YYYY HH:MM:SS UTC.

Name: Timestamp_2
Description: Transmission time of the second vessel's AIS signal. Should be in the form MM/DD/YYYY HH:MM:SS UTC.

Name: LAT_1
Description: This is the latitude of the first vessel.

Name: LON_1
Description: This is the longitude of the first vessel.

Name: SOG_1
Description: This is the speed over ground for the first vessel.

Name: COG_1
Description: This is the course over ground for the first vessel.

Name: Heading_1
Description: This is the heading of the first vessel.

Name: VesselName_1
Description: This is the name of the first vessel.

Name: IMO_1
Description: This is the IMO number of the first vessel.

Name: CallSign_1
Description: This is the call sign of the first vessel.

Name: VesselType_1
Description: This is the vessel type for the first vessel.

Name: Status_1
Description: This is the status of the first vessel.

Name: Length_1
Description: This is the length of the first vessel.

Name: Width_1
Description: This is the width of the first vessel.

Name: Draft_1
Description: This is the draft of the first vessel.

Name: Cargo_1
Description: This is the cargo code of the first vessel.

Name: MMSI_2
Description: This is the Maritime Mobile Service Identity of the second vessel.

Name: BaseDateTime_2
Description: This is the time of the second vessel's AIS transmission. Should be in the form MM/DD/YYYY HH:MM:SS UTC.

Name: LAT_2
Description: This is the latitude of the second vessel.

Name: LON_2
Description: This is the longitude of the second vessel.

Name: SOG_2
Description: This is the speed over ground for the second vessel.

Name: COG_2
Description: This is the course over ground for the second vessel.

Name: Heading_2
Description: This is the heading of second vessel.

Name: VesselName_2
Description: This is the name of the second vessel.

Name: IMO_2
Description: This is the second vessel's IMO number.

Name: CallSign_2
Description: This is the second vessel's call sign.

Name: VesselType_2
Description: This is the second vessel's vessel type.

Name: Status_2
Description: This is the second vessel's status.

Name: Length_2
Description: This is the second vessel's length.

Name: Width_2
Description: This is the second vessel's width.

Name: Draft_2
Description: This is the second vessel's draft.

Name: Cargo_2
Description: This is the second vessel's cargo code.

Name: DateCode
Description: This is vessel's UNIX timestamp rounded to the nearest 10 minutes, for use in discretizing the AIS data in intermediate computations.

Name: Box1_Lat
Description: This is vessel's first bounding box's latitude. Sliding-window 16000yd x 16000yd bounding boxes are used to segment the dataset and are defined by their northwestern corner.

Name: Box1_Long
Description: This is vessel's first bounding box's longitude. Sliding-window 16000yd x 16000yd bounding boxes are used to segment the dataset and are defined by their northwestern corner.

Name: Box2_Lat
Description: This is vessel's second bounding box's latitude. Sliding-window 16000yd x 16000yd bounding boxes are used to segment the dataset and are defined by their northwestern corner.

Name: Box2_Long
Description: This is vessel's second bounding box's longitude. Sliding-window 16000yd x 16000yd bounding boxes are used to segment the dataset and are defined by their northwestern corner.

Name: Box3_Lat
Description: This is vessel's third bounding box's latitude. Sliding-window 16000yd x 16000yd bounding boxes are used to segment the dataset and are defined by their northwestern corner.

Name: Box3_Long
Description: This is vessel's third bounding box's longitude. Sliding-window 16000yd x 16000yd bounding boxes are used to segment the dataset and are defined by their northwestern corner.

Name: Box4_Lat
Description: This is vessel's fourth bounding box's latitude. Sliding-window 16000yd x 16000yd bounding boxes are used to segment the dataset and are defined by their northwestern corner.

Name: Box4_Long
Description: This is vessel's fourth bounding box's longitude. Sliding-window 16000yd x 16000yd bounding boxes are used to segment the dataset and are defined by their northwestern corner.

Name: MMSI
Description: This is the Maritime Mobile Service Identity of the vessel in the AIS report.

Name: BaseDateTime
Description: This is the time of the vessel's AIS transmission. Should be in the form MM/DD/YYYY HH:MM:SS UTC.

Name: LAT
Description: This is the latitude of the vessel.

Name: LON
Description: This is the longitude of the vessel.

Name: SOG
Description: This is the speed over ground for the vessel.

Name: COG
Description: This is the course over ground for the vessel.

Name: Heading
Description: This is the heading of the vessel.

Name: VesselName
Description: This is the name of the vessel.

Name: IMO
Description: This is the International Maritime Organization number of the vessel.

Name: CallSign
Description: This is the call sign of the vessel.

Name: VesselType
Description: This is the vessel type.

Name: Status
Description: This is an optional status of the vessel.

Name: Length
Description: This is the length of the vessel.

Name: Width
